5:
Damn, that is a lot of stuff. Are you
seriously planning on selling ALL of
this?
8:
Of course. It's peak shopping
season, and I plan to sell every last
item in stock. Come on, just a bit
more work to do before we open.
14:
Don't tell me the only reason you
called us out here was because you
were short on staff...
17:
Now, now. You will be
well-compensated for your timely
labor, rest assured.
20:
We're still waiting on a response. Will
you cooperate with us or not?
22:
As you can clearly see, I'm awfully
busy at the moment. I hardly have
the time to chat with the likes of you.
24:
If you affiliate yourself with us, we
can offer you all sorts of places to
do business—
28:
Would you look at that, it's already
time to open the shop! Let's shelve
this conversation for another time.
32:
Anti-royalist rebels? You're tied up
with enemies of the kingdom?
36:
Oh, so those feline ears of yours
aren't just for show, I see.
39:
I wouldn't say I'm "tied up" with them.
I just offer them information I get
while running the caravan.
43:
Aren't you worried people will think
you're part of their organization?
46: That could get ugly real fast.
50:
Relax. I know what I'm doing. I make
sure to maintain a careful distance
at all times.
52:
I don't take risks. My plan is to profit
from peace, after all.
57:
To think that they would come all
this way. I suppose I wasn't direct
enough with my last rejection.
60:
Gah, those crazy punks. I don't need
this right now...
65:
Why'd you call us out so late? I
thought you said to relax until tomo—
68:
The rebels are making a move. We
need to get out of here before we
get caught up in this too.
71:
They're planning on capturing this
town and using it as a bargaining
chip in negotiations. They're going to
take everyone hostage.
75:
They can't be serious... The kingdom
will never go for that. It'll be a
bloodbath...
78:
My thoughts exactly. However,
there's zero reason for me to stick
my neck into this mess.
80:
If I'm going to run, I wanted to take
you all with me—
90:
If we inform the guards, they can
help the people evacuate.
94:
We can't stand by and allow harm
to come to the townspeople. We
must act.
99:
That's right. We don't want to get
you involved in this, so if you're
going to skip town, do it now.
103:
...I'll do just that. I can't afford to let
anything happen to the caravan,
after all.
106: Do you think me a coward?
111:
No.
Please do what you think is right.
115:
Your cooperation is greatly
appreciated. We've informed the
residents—feel free to join them at
the evacuation point.
118:
I suppose we've done all we can for
the time being...
121:
We mustn't let our guard down. The
rebels may still attack the
evacuation shelter.
127: Wait... Where are all the people?
131:
I don't know where you got your
intel, but I'm afraid we can't let you
get in our way.
134: Damn—they had a spy in the guard?!
140:
There's way too many of them to
hold back, Alk.
149:
Not another move! Time for this
buffoonery to come to an end.
152: H-how the hell... Why are YOU here?!
154:
I should be asking you the same
thing. Planning an attack without my
approval—you KNOW this region is
under my control.
157:
Lay down your arms. That's a direct
order. I pray you're not foolish
enough to disobey it.
160:
Well then. I suppose I can leave the
rest to you?
162:
Indeed. You have my gratitude for
your timely warning. I trust you'll
arrange a cover-up for us?
164:
Of course. I'll make up a story about
some quarrel or other.
168:
Tahweel... You didn't evacuate after
all?
171:
Nope. I went and had a chat with a
higher-up from the rebel faction. 
I just let him know his subordinates
were up to no good.
174:
Planning an insurrection like that
without permission from the top
brass is a no-go, you see. I was sure
he'd move to stop them.
178:
Whatever happened to not doing
things unless they benefitted you?
181:
See, that's what I thought at first as
well... Until I considered that
stopping this attack was actually in
my best interests too.
183:
I can't exactly set up my caravan
here if war breaks out, now can I?
188:
Quite the entrepreneurial spirit you
have there... Though I suppose it did
save us from a bind.
192:
To tell you the truth, I mostly did it
because I felt leaving in such a
fashion was... a bad look for me.
194:
Running away like that... would be
like throwing away the promise 
I made to Rolan.
197:
I just... did what I thought was right, 
I suppose.
200:
Because I'm through with having
regrets.
